gomodel:SYNGO_397  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Flotillin-2 regulates in cooperation with Rab11a membrane trafficking processes in spines and participates in LTP-related AMPA receptor (GluA1) surface exposure in mouse hippocampal neurons.\n\n13/4/2017 Pim\nFig.4\n- shRNA KD of Reggie1 or reggie2 results in reduction of surface AMPAR clusters in a protocol of chemical LTP.. Experimental description: Hippocampal neurons from 1 to 2 d old wt C57BL/6J and reggie-1 k.o. (Flot2-/-) mice. (p 32)\nReggie-1 knock-out (k.o.; Flot2 -/-) C57BL/6J mice were generously provided by Tak W. Mak (The Campbell Family Institute for Breast Cancer Research, University Toronto, Canada; Berger et al., 2013). K.o. and wild type (wt) C57BL/6J mice were raised in the animal facility, University of Konstanz. Male and female mice, 1-2 d and 2 months old, were used.\n\n20/3/2017 Pim\n- The species of overexpression constructs used in this paper are not relevant for species determination since they merely serve as specificity controls for KD/KO conditions." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2017-04-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_397" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

